  "texts": [
    "Node clustering constructs a hierarchically coarsened graph by aggregating similar nodes in the graph into new nodes.",
    "The node clustering process is usually performed based on the similarity or connectivity between nodes, aiming to preserve the key structure and feature information in the graph.",
    "The node sampling method selects a subset of significant nodes from the original graph as a basis for building a coarsened graph.",
    "These important nodes may be selected based on the importance, influence, or other specific metrics of the nodes.",
    "The set of nodes obtained through sampling can represent the key structure and information of the original graph, thus constructing a coarsened graph with a hierarchical structure."
  ],
